{"title":"Variance and Volatility of a Three‑Asset Portfolio","markdown":{"headingText":"Variance and Volatility of a Three‑Asset Portfolio","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n```{r}\n#| eval: true\n#| echo: false\n#| results: asis\n#| warning: false\nlibrary(webexercises)\nset.seed(4321)\n# Random weights summing to 1\nw1 <- runif(1, 0, 1)\nw2 <- runif(1, 0, 1 - w1)\nw3 <- 1 - w1 - w2\n# Volatilities (% per year)\nsd1 <- rnorm(1, mean = 15, sd = 3)\nsd2 <- rnorm(1, mean = 20, sd = 4)\nsd3 <- rnorm(1, mean = 25, sd = 5)\n# Correlations between assets\nrho12 <- runif(1, -0.2, 0.8)\nrho13 <- runif(1, -0.2, 0.8)\nrho23 <- runif(1, -0.2, 0.8)\n# Compute variance and standard deviation (squared %)\nvar_port <- w1^2 * sd1^2 + w2^2 * sd2^2 + w3^2 * sd3^2 + 2*w1*w2*sd1*sd2*rho12 + 2*w1*w3*sd1*sd3*rho13 + 2*w2*w3*sd2*sd3*rho23\nsd_port <- sqrt(var_port)\n```\n\nYou invest **`r round(w1*100,2)`%**, **`r round(w2*100,2)`%**, and **`r round(w3*100,2)`%** of your funds in three assets with volatilities **`r round(sd1,2)`%**, **`r round(sd2,2)`%**, and **`r round(sd3,2)`%**, respectively. The pairwise correlations are ρ₁₂ = **`r round(rho12,2)`**, ρ₁₃ = **`r round(rho13,2)`**, and ρ₂₃ = **`r round(rho23,2)`**.\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q9a\"><strong>1. What is the variance of the portfolio?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q9a\" name=\"module3_num_q9a\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=`r round( var_port , 2 )` data-tolerance=\"0.03\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q9a\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n✅ Variance = Σwᵢ²σᵢ² + 2Σ wᵢwⱼσᵢσⱼρᵢⱼ = **`r round(var_port, 2)`**.\n</div>\n\n:::\n\n::: {.question-block}\n\n<form onsubmit=\"event.preventDefault();\" style=\"display: flex; flex-direction: row; gap: 6px;\">\n  <label for=\"module3_num_q9b\"><strong>2. What is the standard deviation of the portfolio (in %)?</strong></label>\n  <input type=\"number\" id=\"module3_num_q9b\" name=\"module3_num_q9b\" placeholder=\"Enter value\" style=\"width: 150px;\"\n         data-correct-answer=`r round( sd_port , 2 )` data-tolerance=\"0.03\" />\n</form>\n\n<div id=\"feedback-module3_num_q9b\" class=\"feedback\" data-status=\"\" style=\"display:none;\">\n✅ Standard deviation = √(variance) = **`r round(sd_port, 2)`**%.\n</div>\n\n:::","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"cache":null,"freeze":false,"echo":true,"output":true,"warning":true,"include":true,"keep-md":false,"keep-ipynb":false,"ipynb":null,"enabled":null,"daemon":null,"daemon-restart":false,"debug":false,"ipynb-filters":[],"ipynb-shell-interactivity":null,"plotly-connected":true,"engine":"knitr"},"render":{"keep-tex":false,"keep-typ":false,"keep-source":false,"keep-hidden":false,"prefer-html":false,"output-divs":true,"output-ext":"html","fig-align":"default","fig-pos":null,"fig-env":null,"code-fold":"none","code-overflow":"scroll","code-link":false,"code-line-numbers":false,"code-tools":false,"tbl-colwidths":"auto","merge-includes":true,"inline-includes":false,"preserve-yaml":false,"latex-auto-mk":true,"latex-auto-install":true,"latex-clean":true,"latex-min-runs":1,"latex-max-runs":10,"latex-makeindex":"makeindex","latex-makeindex-opts":[],"latex-tlmgr-opts":[],"latex-input-paths":[],"latex-output-dir":null,"link-external-icon":false,"link-external-newwindow":false,"self-contained-math":false,"format-resources":[],"notebook-links":true,"canonical-url":"https://henriquemartins.net/"},"pandoc":{"standalone":true,"wrap":"none","default-image-extension":"png","to":"html","css":["../../../../include/webex.css"],"include-after-body":["../../../../inclu